<L>__{exterior dock full shot willard, others}
<A>__{he walks down onto the dock. gaston's men are transferring ammunition boxes. gaston is standing with philippe, who are covering the chief and crew with m 16's.}
<C>__{gaston}
<D>__{two of my men deserted last night. it happens from time to time. i assume my daughter told you of our conditions.}
<C>__{willard}
<D>__{your daughter.}
<C>__{chief}
<D>__{they taking half our ammo, captain said it was your orders.}
<A>__{he pauses for a second.}
<C>__{willard}
<D>__{that's right i did.}
<A>__{the chief spits in the water disgustedly and starts the engines. willard looks hard at gaston.}
<C>__{willard}
<D>__{i guess this is what men of war do eh?}
<C>__{gaston}
<D>__{we endure, captain you can blow up the house and we will live in the cellar destroy that and we'll dig a hole in the jungle and sleep on it. burn the forest and we'll hide in the swamp. all the while, we do but one thing clean the blood off our bayonets.}
<P>__{(pause)}
<D>__{au revoir, captain.}
